# This one counts up from the first numbers in the sequence until it hits the number you want
def fibCountUpWithRecursion(n, i, num1, num2):
    num3 = num1 + num2
    if i == n-2:  # Base case is very similar to loop conditions on lines 60 and 46
        return num3
    elif i == 1 and n == 1 or n == 2:  # Base case is similar to base cases on lines 65 and 51
        return 1
    return fibCountUpWithRecursion(n, i + 1, num2, num3)  # Recursive call
